<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-1583] Document maxClientCnxns in conf/zoo_sample.cfg</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-1583</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is silly that maxClientCnxns being set to the default, and that default being too low, is the number one issue for users (according to some: &lt;a href=&quot;https://raw.github.com/strangeloop/strangeloop2012/master/slides/sessions/Ting-BuildingAnImpenetrableZooKeeper.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://raw.github.com/strangeloop/strangeloop2012/master/slides/sessions/Ting-BuildingAnImpenetrableZooKeeper.pdf&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems to me that this can be resolved by an extremely simple documentation change: add a commented-out configuration line in conf/zoo_sample.cfg that shows the default, but more importantly, shows users that the configuration option exists.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
